summary:
As COO at Better Talent, I act as the integrator that leads the team that leverages technology, behavioral science, and human touch to identify and hire the right talent for organizations. 

With a depth of experience in leading and managing teams, I'm driven by a passion for living out core values, staying focused on the vision, simplicity, and clarity to ultimately dramatically reduce friction for customers and employees alike. I'm a growth-minded problem solver who excels at attracting, retaining, and developing high-performing teams that are focused on the bottom line.

My expertise lies in identifying areas of opportunity for increased profitability through revenue growth, increased margin, and cost reduction. With a background in tech, I am skilled at using technology to streamline operations and improve productivity. I thrive in fast-paced and innovative environments, and my range of skills in sales strategy and growth makes me adaptable to new businesses and strategic initiatives, which benefits our Better Talent customers immensely. 
Above all, I'm known for my empathy and ability to influence with integrity. Let's connect and explore how to work together to achieve your organization's goals.

summary:
A possible summary is:

As the COO at MarketJoy, a leading B2B marketing agency, I am responsible for the complete operations and development of the company's growth. I spearhead top-line and bottom-line revenue growth, devising strategies to produce sustainable results. I also proactively engage with CEOs, marketing heads, and IT heads of our clients, to chart and execute an engagement roadmap that meets their expectations and goals.

With a Bachelor of Business Administration from SHUATS and over 7 years of experience in the B2B marketing industry, I have developed skills in demand generation, digital strategy, content marketing, SEO, lead generation, marketing automation, and multi-channel marketing. I manage and coach a team of operations and business development professionals, empowering them to identify training needs and grow the company. My mission is to lead the business to higher growth and build powerful brands that last for generations.

summary:
Leo is a serial entrepreneur in the tech industry. Built a UX design agency to seven figures, delivering 130+ high-performing products used by 30M+ users. Co-founded a VC-backed AI marketplace connecting brands with influencers. Vast operator experience, having built multiple business functions in sales, product, design and development. Proven track record operating 4 different business models: consultancy, SaaS, marketplaces and digital products.

As a co-founder at Curvo, he is reducing the rep productivity gap and redefining the future of sales. A squad of expert AI sales agents for revenue acceleration. Deal insights are based on sales playbooks with enterprise sales frameworks, highlighting key risks in deals so reps can make better decisions.
headline: Co-founder at Curvo - Deal intelligence for enterprise sales teams to maximise revenue potential.

summary:
I am a leading Account Executive and a recent college graduate, passionate about making connections, building relationships, and understanding client needs. My motivation, drive, and ambition are to build robust pipelines, qualify leads, schedule appointments, and close deals that will increase revenue and achieve target goals and objectives. I’ve learned and utilized a variety of sales methods, including cold calling, messaging on platforms such as LinkedIn, and sending email campaigns.

As an honors student and having worked throughout my collegiate studies, I know what hard work and dedication can achieve. As an SDR with DearDoc, I was quickly promoted after three months and have been recognized for meeting and exceeding target quotas. My consultative approach to driving business vision, connecting with prospects, and collaborating with team members in fast-paced settings, has proven to be highly effective in achieving quotas of 300 cold calls per day and scheduling meetings and demos.

summary:
👋 Hi there! I'm Kaavia Kanesalingam, a passionate Customer Success Manager with a knack for building strong relationships and driving results. My journey in customer success and sales has been a thrilling adventure filled with learning, growth, and numerous wins. Here's a snapshot of my story:

🔹 Customer Success Manager at Xello: I currently oversee renewals for a $1.2 million book of business, develop strategies to enhance product adoption, and partner with clients to create success plans. My role is all about ensuring clients achieve their goals and love the products we offer.

🔹 Account Executive at SearchKings: I thrived in the fast-paced world of Google advertising, identifying sales opportunities, upselling to existing customers, and maintaining strong relationships with over 300 accounts. My efforts consistently exceeded KPIs and placed me among the top performers on my team.

🔹 Creative Recruiter at Vitamin T - Aquent: I recruited top talent for roles in technology, design, marketing, advertising, and communications. My ability to build and maintain relationships helped generate significant revenue and foster team unity.

💼 With a Bachelor of Science and Business from the University of Waterloo and a Certificate in Digital Strategy & Communications Management from the University of Toronto, I blend technical know-how with strategic insights to drive success.

🚀 I'm not just about work. I'm also an avid hiker, an acrylic canvas painter, and a sports enthusiast who loves playing touch football, flag football, volleyball, and ultimate frisbee. Traveling is my other passion, with memorable trips to Sri Lanka, India, and Peru.

Technologies:  MS Office, CloudWall, Google Ads, Google Local Services, Ease, BullHorn, Tableau, Fieldglass, BeeLine, Canva, Mail Chimp, Google Analytics, WordPress, Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, Eventbrite, SharePoint, TelusHealth, JaneApp, LinkedIn Recruiter and BluePrint

summary:
Welcome to the world of Mr. Isak Hodges 👋

 - a dynamic young professional who is eager to make his mark in the global business landscape. My background in Political Science has equipped me with a deep understanding of global affairs, and my keen interest in international relations has inspired me to pursue a career that allows me to make a positive impact on the world.

In my previous roles, I have gained extensive experience in customer management, sales development, and building strong business-client relationships. These skills have equipped me with the ability to effectively communicate with clients and colleagues from a variety of backgrounds, as well as to adapt quickly to new situations and environments.

As a well-travelled individual who has lived in 8 countries across 3 continents, I bring a unique global perspective to my work. I have visited over 35 countries and am passionate about learning about new cultures, trying new foods, and experiencing new ways of life. My travel experiences have taught me how to be adaptable, flexible, and open-minded, which are all essential skills for any professional working in an increasingly globalized business environment.

In my professional career, I am committed to building strong relationships with my colleagues and clients. I believe that the key to success in any business is to foster positive and productive relationships, and I am dedicated to working collaboratively to achieve our shared goals.

I am excited to explore new opportunities that will challenge and enable me to continue developing both personally and professionally. Thank you for taking the time to learn more about me.

💼 Currently: Student Pilot @ Pacific Flying Club

Passions: ✈ | ⛷ | 🗣 | 🏃 | 🏍 | 🍕 | 🏎 | 🎵

An outdoor enthusiast 🌲 I spend most of my weekends finding time to get into nature, and enjoy the beautiful world that we live in. 

📜 My favourite quote: "Enjoy the butterflies. Enjoy being naive. Enjoy the nerves, the pressure, people not knowing your name, all that stuff." - Daniel Ricciardo 

✉ Connect with me: I always want to expand my network, so shoot my a request! Tell me your craziest travel story, your biggest leap of faith, or simply your best pasta recipe.
headline: Student Pilot @ Pacific Flying Club 🛩️🛩️🛩️

summary:
As the founder of Better Talent, I'm excited to share our game-changing hiring solution with you. Our innovative platform, combined with our exceptional team, is revolutionizing the recruitment process in the hospitality industry.

After 34 years of forming and growing various businesses, I've come to a crucial realization: the key to success lies in identifying, hiring, and engaging the right people. When the right individuals are in the right roles and fully engaged, we've achieved remarkable success. Without this, even the most brilliant strategic plans fall short.

We specialize in outsourced talent acquisition for the hospitality sector, including vacation rentals, restaurants, hotels, and housekeeping companies. Our comprehensive approach includes:

- Optimizing job postings
- Providing broad exposure on top job sites
- Matching candidates based on skills and personality

Our innovative screening system pre-assesses candidates, allowing hiring managers to focus on a select pool of high-quality applicants. We also offer our clients access to our proprietary talent platform for managing the entire hiring process.

About me:

I've spent the last 28 years deeply immersed in the rapidly growing vacation rental industry. Throughout my career, I've:

- Founded 16 companies, mostly revolving around the vacation rental industry
- Been involved in various aspects of the sector, including marketing, management, business development, and software development
- Served on the board of several industry associations, including five years as Vice President and then President of the Vacation Rental Manager Association (VRMA)
- Led initiatives such as launching a PR campaign and a reality television series, and expanding into the European market

Currently, I serve multiple organizations across the industry in an advisory capacity, hold equity positions, and sit on advisory boards.

Our Commitment to You

At Better Talent, we're not just another recruiting company or staffing agency. We're an outsourced Talent Acquisition and Optimization Team dedicated to providing significant value while helping you build the best team possible.

I'm passionate about leveraging my experiences - both good and bad - to help companies and individuals in this space. Having hired many recruiters in my career, I understand the importance of bringing real value to our clients. That's why at Better Talent, we're disrupting the recruiting model to provide massive value while helping build the very best teams.
headline: Changing the (HIRING) game!

summary:
With a Diploma in Business Administration from Capilano University and a degree from the National University of Ireland, Galway, my educational background laid the foundation for my role as an Account Executive at Bench Accounting. Here, my core competencies in account management and client services have been vital in cultivating customer satisfaction and securing an average of 20 new clients monthly.

Since joining Bench Accounting, my focus has been on full-cycle sales, managing both inbound and outbound strategies with a heavier emphasis on the former. My experience in B2B deals, predominantly in the USA, has been integral to surpassing performance goals, with a notable 143% attainment in 2023. Working within our team, I've fostered strategic partnerships that have been pivotal in closing deals, highlighting my commitment to collaborative success and contributing to our united goal of driving growth and excellence in SMB sales.

summary:
Helping students discover a new era of personalized learning, tailored to the individuals unique academic journey. 

Every day students go into the classroom where professors have no idea who they are, where they come from, and the challenges specific to them...

Sia remedies this. Our platform understands each student over time and gives them precision education that will improve not just academic performance, but also their efficiency outside the classroom.

We've developed a platform that collects personalized data over time to help us understand how students learn and support them when they're studying with content and resources that are tailored for them.

Want to explore? DM me here or send me an email to psri@builder.ai

summary:
Dynamic Head of Operations with a demonstrated history of cultivating robust customer support ecosystems. At Voyc, my mission has been to innovate customer experiences, evidenced by spearheading the establishment of a customer support function from the ground up, now expanding to a team of three. I've been instrumental in slashing response times from hours to under 15 minutes and driving customer advocacy through attentive support and strategic automations.

I thrive in environments that value progression and out-of-the-box thinking, and my journey at Voyc has been a testament to that, rapidly progressing through roles and responsibilities. My approach balances the efficiency of automation with the irreplaceable human touch, resulting in significant improvements in customer satisfaction and operational efficiency.

I am always bringing my experience in operational excellence and customer-centric innovations to companies while continuing to grow and tackle new challenges.

summary:
I am an ex-big 4 auditor and an experienced finance professional with 8 years of finance experience. Have been recently serving as a Fractional CFO for small to medium trucking companies and helping startups raise money. Skilled in Business Development, Auditing, IFRS, Corporate Finance, Financial Modeling, and Startup Finance. ACCA candidate - Part qualified (11 out of 13)

MBA candidate at the Simon Business School with outstanding academic performance. My experience also includes exposure to banking and non-banking financial institutions, metallurgy, oil and gas, IT, transportation, and service industries.

First mnemonist and leader in Uzbekistan in spreading mnemonics among the youth, designing educational courses and curriculum, and teaching more than 1,000 individuals. Author of three books on self-development.

summary:
I co-founded TekStack with my good friend James Patterson in 2019.  We previously worked together growing a software company. Overlapping for a few years, me as CRO, James as COO; we were able to grow that business to a significant enough size, with over 1000 customers, 8 offices, 250 employees.  

Along that journey we realized just how hard it was to create an integrated revenue operation.  We had a massive technology stack and a bunch of people supporting it.  Prepping for a board meeting was a joke.  Everything was in Excel.  We figured there had to be a better way to run a profitable technology business.

So that's why we created TekStack.  TekStack is the thing we always wanted to have to run our past businesses.  It replaces platforms like Salesforce, HubSpot, or ConnectWise with a fully integrated app from first touch all the way through customer upsell, and every step in between.  

Most CRMs are a joke.  The "C" should stand for "Prospect" because the minute an account becomes a customer, the data dies on the vine.

We fix this by integrating all departments on one platform.  Think marketing, sales, project services, customer support, customer success, renewal management, and billing.  Replace 10 systems with one.  Everything powered by Microsoft Cloud.   Priced right.  Backed by process expertise.  We even provide managed services so you can focus on high value team building, not back office operations.

There is so much pressure on tech companies to grow more efficiently.  Revenue Operations is key to this but putting in proper tech, insights, and supporting team can feel like a monumental task.  We want to fix that.  

I see RevOps a little like electricity in your home.  It lies beneath the surface, super boring stuff, but can enable so much.

I love to grow technology companies.  I've done it as a marketer, seller, and P&L leader for 25 years now.  

On the personal front, I'm a dad. Former Ironman and triathlete.  Try to stay in shape with cycling, running, swimming, and yoga.  Split time between Toronto and New York.

summary:
>>>𝒎𝒐𝒉𝒂𝒎𝒎𝒆𝒅𝒉.𝒄𝒐<<< 𝑪𝒉𝒆𝒄𝒌 𝒊𝒕 𝒐𝒖𝒕

I build things. I automate things. I visualise things. I do this all at scale.

I am a senior finance professional with 8+ years of international experience in FP&A, strategic finance, financial analysis, and corporate finance.
I have worked in 2 countries, lived in 6 cities, and travelled across more than 20 cities. I plan to grow these numbers year-on-year.
I am adept at helping leadership execute its strategic, operational, and financial goals. I have scaled the financial modelling capabilities of large and small companies (Amazon, BCA, etc.) across multiple industries.
My achievements have shown I can learn, at speed, the landscape of an organisation, and optimise and scale.

I spent my formative years specialising as a financial modeller and business partner.
I implement financial modelling best practises (like FAST) whilst optimising reporting and budgeting capabilities. I optimise by centralising the financial modelling function, standardising best practices for creating models, and automating process flows through Power Query and BI.
I serve as a coach to the next-gen of interns to improve their technical skills as well as soft skills.
I have implemented Wim Hof meditation inside of companies as well as externally. I have led guided meditation sessions throughout Luxembourg City, Barcelona, and the UK. I personally implement Wim Hof as a framework to manage short and long-term stressors.

At the backend/start of 2021/2022 i took time out to recentre, focus on myself, personal projects, and to plan the next 5 years of my career. Wim Hof was and continues to be beneficial. I am now excited for my next journey and new role!

Finance tech stack: Financial Modelling (Excel, Google Sheets, Power Query, VBA), PowerBI (inc. DAX), SQL,  Netsuite, Xero, COGNOS, TM1, R.

Fun Fact 1: My Favourite tech skill is Power Query. It reshaped how i approach designing a data model and problem-solving.

Fun Fact 2: I am a writer for FP&A Trends Group. You can access my articles at https://fpa-trends.com/author/mohammed-hussain.

Languages: English, Urdu (mother tongue), French (conversational), Spanish (learning)

Happy to connect with like-minded individuals. And please, if I can be of value do not hesitate to message me ! :)

summary:
A results oriented Sales Professional with continuing experience in highly competitive markets.  Proven track record of providing solutions in challenging business scenarios with leveraging relationships and utilizing value-based frameworks to drive strategic goals and objectives. Transferrable skills from multiple industries with a specialization in SaaS.  Big sports analytics guy, Seahawks. 13.2 Handicap Index 🏌🏼‍♂️

​“Try Again. Fail Again. Fail Better.” - Samuel Beckett

Always open to connect!

Can't Hurt Me - David Goggins

Ego is the Enemy - Ryan Holiday

headline: Founder & CEO at ThoroughCare
experience: [{'locationName': 'Pittsburgh, PA', 'entityUrn': 'urn:li:fs_position:(ACoAAAE4DzcBUV_GaWveuvNUSLd6SoYwrf0YeQo,420575100)', 'geoLocationName': 'Pittsburgh, PA', 'companyName': 'ThoroughCare, Inc.', 'timePeriod': {'startDate': {'month': 7, 'year': 2013}}, 'description': 'Founded ThoroughCare to fill the need for an efficient patient assessment product for the healthcare industry.  After being chosen for the 2013 IronYard digital healthcare accelerator, ThoroughCare was officially launch. My leadership extends globally, covering territories including EMEA, US, UK, and ANZ, where I've ensured that our sales approach remains professional and positive, providing best-in-class support. summary:
I am an easy-going & dedicated person with a passion for business and entrepreneurship. Growing up, hockey and sports played a significant role in my life, fostering my enthusiasm for leadership, mentorship, and training. I consider myself a lifelong learner, always curious and open to new opportunities and knowledge.

I enjoy outdoor activities, travelling, and experiencing all that life has to offer. I am continually striving to improve myself, pursue my passions, and make a lasting impact on everything I work on.

Currently, I work as an Account Manager at a FinTech SaaS company, where I am responsible for meeting sales quotas and managing client relationships. Additionally, I own and operate a hockey school in the lower mainland, combining my love for sports with my commitment to mentorship and training.

My long-term goals include making a positive impact in my business and corporate ventures, coaching and mentoring people from all walks of life, and travelling the world to experience its diverse cultures.

summary:
Almost two decades of Cost Segregation experience coupled with software UX and product management experience, I founded SegStream to attack the many inefficiencies around producing Cost Segregation studies.

After focusing exclusively on helping professional Cost Segregation engineers to start, we've pivoted to create the very first Cost Segregation automation software designed for Accounting and Specialty Tax Professionals.

We believe that, with a focus on innovation, we can make Cost Segregation increasingly more efficient and higher in quality every day.

summary:
As an expert in student recruitment, I empower UK universities to excel in the competitive higher education landscape through our innovative Student CRM platform. I specialise in fostering strong relationships and leveraging personal data, communication technologies, and data protection to generate high-value prospects and enrolled students.

With our powerful CRM, UK student recruitment teams can experience the following benefits:

1. Engage Prospective Students with Targeted, Personalised Communication: Strengthen connections by sending tailored content, such as open-day invitations to local prospects, boosting interest in your university.

2. Streamline Recruitment Processes and Workflows: Automate tasks like sending follow-up emails after an open day, freeing up time for your team to focus on building relationships with students.

3. Harness Data Analytics for Strategic Decision-Making: Identify trends in applicant demographics and preferences, optimising your marketing strategies accordingly.

4. Seamlessly Integrate with Existing Systems: Connect our CRM with your current systems, such as your student information system, ensuring a smooth transition and maximised data value.

5. Track and Nurture Leads Throughout the Recruitment Funnel: Monitor prospective students' journey, from initial enquiry to enrolment, and send timely, relevant communication at every stage.

6. Stay Compliant with GDPR and Data Security: Protect students' data with our platform's built-in data protection and compliance features, ensuring peace of mind for your institution.

7. Measure ROI and Monitor Key Performance Indicators: Evaluate your recruitment success with real-time tracking of KPIs, such as conversion rates, enabling continuous improvement and maximising ROI.

I collaborate with a dedicated team of problem-solvers at a leading UK technology company, where we provide universities with cutting-edge student recruitment software. Our solutions not only help universities achieve their recruitment goals but also seamlessly integrate best practices into their communication strategies.

Visit our website: http://www.student-crm.co.uk

As a driven and energetic leader, I am committed to delivering a 5-star service to our educational clients from our UK offices. Our SaaS solution, 'Student CRM,' boasts a 98% satisfaction rating, making it the UK's most loved student CRM.

Our success is built on continuous investment in our team, technology, and clients, ensuring unparalleled results for universities seeking exceptional student recruitment strategies."
headline: Empowering UK Universities with Cutting-Edge CRM Solutions at student-crm.co.uk | Visionary Founder & Leader | Student Recruitment Advocate | Tech Enthusiast | GDPR Expert | #StudentCRM

summary:
My first selling experience was at 8 years old. I sacrificed playing on my Nintendo DS to build my first e-commerce website. My sales strategy was simple, an early version of “network marketing”. I used sales and persuasion strategies to convince my email contact list (my family) why they should visit my e-commerce website.

I then obtained sales experience in a variety of areas, including going door to door for a home service company I owned, telemarketing, product advising at Best Buy, and was eventually offered an opportunity to work at Bench as a co-op student. After exceeding my quota month over month and going above and beyond for my clients, I received a permanent contract. While surpassing my quota (and accelerators) I achieved the Dean’s List at university. My hard work quickly paid off, earning my stripes and becoming a closer. 

Closing to me has been my form of art. I love using solution selling techniques to customize my experience with every individual prospect. I really enjoy going into a sales call, diving deep into a prospect’s pain points and assessing where I can help solve their problems. 

Everyday I aim to work on my craft just as Stephen Curry does with his three pointers and Leonardo DiCaprio does with acting. 

You can find me reading a book, watching a sales training video or practicing mock calls with colleagues to make sure that come game time, I can perform at the highest level. I take pride in not only learning but applying what I learned to sales calls.

When I am not in a sales environment, I am working hard at the gym, playing sports, or reading.

summary:
I work with a great team at IOTAP across different regions worldwide. I am a Dynamics CRM enthusiast and use it to run our business. We are a first hand case study on Digital Transformation with our Cloud Solutions business. I am eager to share our story and journey with customers and other partners. For Microsoft we an ISV, VAR, SI, CSP - whole bunch of stuff that doesn't matter to our customers! We have just tried different things to make our business run and in the process developed some great insights, processes, services, tools and applications! 

Specialties: Dynamics 365, Customer Engagement, Customer Service, Cloud Services, Office 365, CSP

summary:
As the Founder & CEO of Veza Digital, I’ve always believed that growth isn’t just about scaling—it’s about building ecosystems that thrive. What started as a passion for digital marketing and growth has transformed into leading one of the most dynamic and fast-growing Webflow agencies in the industry.

At Veza Digital, we don’t just build websites—we create powerful marketing websites that drive growth for B2B SaaS companies and beyond. Our mission? To push the boundaries of what’s possible in the space, using Webflow as a base to redefine how companies connect with their customers.

In the last few years, we’ve achieved:

- Strategic acquisitions that have expanded our services and reach.
- Landing enterprise clients that trust us to deliver marketing websites and campaigns that scale.
- Creating Vezafy, a groundbreaking platform that connects Webflow agencies with high-value clients, revolutionizing how the Webflow community does business.

My focus has always been on strategic growth through M&A, pushing innovation, and ensuring that our clients are equipped with the tools they need to succeed. I’m passionate about scaling businesses, building strong teams, and leading with a vision that always looks to the future.

Whether you’re a startup looking for a strategic marketing partner, an agency interested in acquisition opportunities, or a company ready to take your Webflow presence to the next level, I’m always open to new conversations and possibilities.

Let’s build something great together.
headline: Founder & CEO at Veza Digital | Leading Innovation in Webflow & B2B SaaS | Strategic Growth | Building the Future of Webflow Agencies

I invent things and create products to solve problems, at work and at home. My skills include digital and physical prototyping, rapid development of digital and physical products, manufacturer sourcing, and fostering innovative culture within the teams I lead.

summary:
Skilled in talent, development, inclusion, performance and employee engagement and an entrepreneurial, passionate leader. I created Unleashed to provide a suite of education and consultancy services and co-founded Talent Mapper to provide inclusive talent management technology to help organisations to improve their performance and inclusivity. 
 
With a successful background in corporate Talent Management and Learning and Development, I thrive on enabling individuals to grow, to develop their skills and knowledge and to reach their full potential. 

At Talent Mapper, we utilise ground-breaking AI technology to enable organisations to recognise, manage, up-skill and deploy their talent with ease and in an equitable and transparent way, so that they can create an agile, high-performing and motivated workforce.

I enjoy networking and collaborating with people, in the global community of Human Resources, Talent Management and Equality, Diversity & Inclusion professionals, so please feel free to get in touch at martin@thetalentmapper.com

summary:
I’m a senior executive with 20+ years of experience in sales, operations and management.  From carrying a bag to leading a team or running a business - I’ve been fortunate to work cross functionally across the business and partner with great teammates and great customers while having fun along the way.  

I’ve been afforded extensive experience evaluating, completing, and integrating acquisitions, defining competitive advantages, and leading profitable growth.  

Lastly, I love a good team.  Whether building one from scratch or joining a winner and finding new ways to contribute, being part of a good team and a company steeped in positive culture is non-negotiable. 

Specialties: 
C-suite relationships, B2B, Operations, Strategy, Building Teams, P&L, Sales and Marketing, SaaS

summary:
CEO and founder at Swiftlane. 
https://swiftlane.com/

Swiftlane works with property managers and multifamily owners to:
- Provide new technology upgrades to apartment and condo buildings
- Attract GenZ and Millenial renters through modern mobile first amenities
- Automate and centralize building access management and removing that hassle for property managers
- Eliminate package theft and break-ins
- Give technology superpowers to drive higher yield and manage 10X more buildings
- Provide cutting edge access control and video intercom systems

Deployed in 1000+ apartment communities across the US. I am looking to hire people across all roles. We are growing at a break-neck pace and looking for people who are interested in driving disproportional impact. 

Notable Investors: Bloomberg Beta, Caffeinated Capital, Scifi VC, Hike VC, Elad Gil, Scott Belsky, Max Levchin.

summary:
Two years ago I switched careers.

From private chef to SDR in SaaS sales. Quite the course shift.

Never one to shy away from a challenge, I put all efforts towards acheiving success.

Wow what a ride. 

What I learned through that time was that no matter what you acheive, there's always room to improve. I love the challenge and process of practice, implementation, reflection and improvement.

Outside of professional me, I'm a father of two, husband to one. Once a chef, always a chef. Mountain biker, skiier, outdoors and nature guy.

summary:
I am a recent Bucknell University graduate with a major in Computer Engineering. I have a keen interest in building catered software products for customers, specifically doing development on the backend. 
I have prior experience in high-level team-based SaaS and freelance work, and am interested in full-time career opportunities that will continue to challenge me as a software engineer. 

Technical Skills: Python, Java, Angular, AWS full-stack, MongoDB, SQL, HTML/CSS, GitLab (CI/CD)

Other Skills: Scrum methodology, teamwork, communication/public-speaking, competitive mindset

summary:
I am the Chief Operating Officer of Case Status, a legal tech software that helps law firms change the way they engage with their clients.  Case Status streamlines client communications, provides real-time case progress tracking, facilitates NPS & referrals, and improves the client experience.  

Prior to relocating to Charleston, SC and joining Case Status in 2023, I was the CEO at Envoque, an employee engagement consultancy working with companies to help improve their employee experience.  Additionally, I've also served as the SEVP and Head of North America at Tivian, a global leader in employee engagement solutions, where I led the growth and expansion of the business in the region.  I also have a strong background in software/solution development, customer success, digital/brand marketing and large-scale content and creative production, having worked as the Senior VP Solutions and Head of Studios at GuideSpark, the Chief Digital Officer at Mod Op, and the COO and Managing Partner at Creative Asylum.  I have published articles on topics such as employee communications, content strategy, and QSR industry trends in various media outlets.  My core competencies include strategic leadership, complete company operations, marketing innovation, digital transformation, and customer satisfaction.

summary:
I’m a builder and a cyclist. I love to push myself. There is nothing more satisfying than the accomplishment of something you’ve created or a difficult goal you've achieved.

As an infant, I loved Lego - all the pieces, all the possibilities. As a child, I was captivated by models and RC kits – intricately painted and painstakingly assembled. As a young man, computers supplanted model kits opening my eyes to endless possibilities.

As a professional, I channeled my inner builder into developing web applications with Accenture. When I joined Resolver in 2004 as employee number 5, I had the extraordinary experience of building both a great product and a great company. 

Now, I’m on to another challenge, starting a new software company, TekStack. It feels strange to go back to the beginning, however, I’m doing what I’m passionate about: building great products, delivering exceptional solutions, creating happy, raving customers and cycling with my colleagues.

I hold a Bachelor of Commerce from McGill University. I live in Toronto with my wife and two kids. In my spare time, I love hanging out with my family, playing sports, riding my bicycle insanely long distances, and, of course, building stuff … mostly bicycles and Lego with my son.

summary:
People and Software Based Solutions to your Recruitment, Training and Ops challenges.

I have worked in healthcare recruitment and staffing for over 20 years in the UK and Australia.  I lead H1 Healthcare Group, a family business providing care and nurse staffing, home and complex care services.

I built Qintil as a learning, recruitment and rostering platform for H1 because we couldn't find a complete solution that worked for us.  Our business has grown rapidly since then and Qintil is now used by hundreds of other health and home care business as well as by employers and staffing agencies in industries likes security, telecoms, logistics and retail.

How can I help you?

I love working with businesses who need solutions to their recruitment and people ops challenges.

Get in touch to discuss:

- How I can help with you recruit and retain great people 
- Streamlining your learning and development operations 
- Hiring faster and with greater visibility at scale
- Recruitment, staffing and rostering solutions that helps you place people quickly and compliantly
- Business growth and scaling challenges

Who I'd love to meet

I am always keen to make new connections with business owners and operators in people driven businesses.  Please do get in touch if you've got something I might be interested in or would like to discuss anything above.
headline: Helping solve People Ops challenges in the industries we all rely on.  CEO Qintil and H1 Healthcare Group.  Supporting Employers and Staffing Agencies with Recruitment, Learning and Staffing solutions and software.

summary: As a Customer Success Manager and Team Lead at DearDoc, I helped oversee a team of customer success managers who assist healthcare providers grow their practices through online marketing and patient communication. I have been working at DearDoc for over two years now, starting as a Sales Development Representative and then moving up to a Customer Success Manager and Team Lead. I have a proven track record of increasing customer retention, satisfaction, and loyalty, as well as generating new sales opportunities and referrals I've actively contributed to various strategic initiatives, including overseeing an in-depth analysis of a flagship product. I conducted beta testing to establish a more streamlined approach for client outreach, enabling our team to enhance efficiency. Additionally, this initiative facilitated comprehensive learning and implementation of best practices within our customer success team. I have acquired multiple skills in customer success management, customer engagement, sales, and marketing, and I am always eager to learn new things and take on new challenges.
